and redistribute by email or post to the web.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 India plans to make \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  obligatory for mining companies in reaction to concern over pollution and rebel violence.\par \par \uc2 Santha Sheela Nair, the secretary at the mines ministry, said on Sunday that a draft Mines and Minerals (Development & Regulation) Act sought to address the breakdown in trust between mining companies and communities.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 She said the law would enforce corporate responsibility programmes to provide employment and development.\par \par \uc2 In the face of a Maoist insurgency that claimed the lives of almost 80 soldiers in one attack last month, the plans were crucial for "conflict management and resolution" in a battle between rival corporate and civilian cultures.\par \par \uc2 Mining companies operating in India should make their local stakeholders also their shareholders to overcome hostility towards the industry, she said but warned that negative perceptions of mining would have to be overcome. The draft legislation contains proposals to offer equity to communities whose land is acquired for mining projects.\par \par \uc2 India is the fourth-largest iron ore producer in the world and has significant deposits of coal, bauxite and chromite. Local mining companies include listed companies such as Sesa Goa, Sterlite, Tata and the \uc2 Steel Authority of India\uc2 . They also number less internationally known iron ore miners such as \uc2 Obulapuram Mining\uc2  and Anantapur Mining, owned by the Reddy political dynasty in Karnataka.\par \par \uc2 Industry experts said mining standards in India lagged global practice by as much as three decades. They warned that poor regulation has given free rein to illegal mining which is harmful to people and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The New York-based Blacksmith Institute ranks the Sukinda valley in Orissa, an iron ore-producing area, alongside Chernobyl, the Ukrainian site of the nuclear accident, as one of the most polluted places on earth.\par \par \uc2 Ms Nair said mining companies needed to repair urgently a "serious conflict of interest" with tribal communities. Referring to the growing Maoist insurrection in five states, she said the conflict had "turned extremely violent". Ms Nair told delegates at a seminar hosted by the Canadian government that tribal people "see mining as a loss of livelihood, loss of life and loss of the relationship with nature that they are used to".\par \par \uc2 The Indian government is realising quickly that uncontrolled mining, often involving politicians, has fuelled a rural rebellion in tribal areas. Some leaders of the ruling Congress party also said mining companies had become prey to protection rackets run by rebels.\par \par \uc2 PC Chidambaram, the home minister, has offered to suspend memorandums of understanding signed with mining companies in an effort to secure a truce with rebels and bring their leaders to the negotiating table.\par \par \uc2 Some industry leaders argued that stronger implementation of existing laws is needed as much as new ones. Nik Senapati, the managing director of Rio Tinto India, said a country might have reams of laws governing corporate conduct but at the end of the day it was enforcement that would improve mining standards.\par \par \uc2 This week, the Survey of India gave the Supreme Court evidence of illegal mining showing that \uc2 Obulapuram Mining\uc2  had extended operations in an environmentally sensitive area beyond its lease in Andhra Pradesh across the border into Karnataka.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20100502_1762_43.xml\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i3251 : \uc2 Mining/Oil/Gas Field Machinery | iindstrls : \uc2 Industrials | i32 : \uc2 Machinery/Industrial Goods\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr