antly diminished the potential value of the instrument", it said.\par \par \uc2 Roel Nieuwenkamp, chair of the OECD investment committee working party in charge of the update of the guidelines, said there was scope for improvements.\par \par \uc2 "The OECD guidelines have been a big contributor to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the world. The conclusion we share with OECD Watch is we can do better," he said.\par \par \uc2 The revisions to the guidelines, which will be debated by businesses, unions, non-governmental organisations and governments, are expected to focus on human rights, sustainable supply-chain management and the way governments promote the guidelines and handle complaints.\par \par \uc2 OECD Watch said: "If no drastic improvements are achieved, civil society will be forced to look elsewhere to resolve the key problems facing affected peoples and the natural \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ."\par \par \uc2 It criticised a failure of many government bodies responsible for investigating complaints. Joseph Wilde-Ramsing of OECD Watch said only five of the 96 cases filed by NGOs had resulted in real improvements in corporate behaviour, although useful recommendations had been made in another 10 cases. A further 117 cases have been brought by trade unions during the past decade.\par \par \uc2 Pierre Poret, head of the OECD investment division, said many cases were resolved by mediation, citing a recent example in which \uc2 Unilever\uc2 , the multinational, agreed to create 200 permanent positions at one of its Pakistan factories after a union complaint. He said that 160 requests for mediation had been accepted out of 220 cases raised during the past 10 years.\par \par \uc2 New measures on the corporate responsibility to protect human rights in the supply chain are set to build on work by Professor John Ruggie, special representative of the UN secretary-general. Companies will face more explicit requirements to monitor abuses such as the use of bonded or child labour in the supply chain, although their responsibilities are likely to depend on how much leverage they can exert on their suppliers.\par \par \uc2 The guidelines, which were introduced in 1976 and last updated in 2000, require member states, along with Argentina, Brazil and Egypt, to nominate government departments or independent organisations to deal with complaints about companies operating or headquartered in their countries.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20100701_21693_307.xml\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 oecode : \uc2 Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \l