\trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (Copyright (c) 2011, Dow Jones & Company, Inc.)    \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 When Marcia Scheiner left a New York financial services company last summer after 25 years in the industry, she negotiated that $250,000 from her severance be donated to charity.\par \par \uc2 Now, she's directing that gift to the Asperger Syndrome Training & Employment Partnership, a nonprofit she is launching this month to help young adults with Asperger syndrome find jobs.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The move is sparked by her son, now in his first year of college. She says a generation of young adults with Asperger's in their 20s and 30s will for the first be heading to college and getting master's degrees but will still be faced with high unemployment rates.\par \par \uc2 According to estimates from the National Institutes of Health, two out of 10,000 children have the disease, which sits on the autism spectrum of disorders. However, Asperger syndrome wasn't widely known until the 1980s.\par \par \uc2 While there's no cure for the disease, effective therapeutic treatments have emerged to help patients with Asperger's maintain independent lives.\par \par \uc2 "From the time they are children, we've allowed them to develop a tremendous amount of skills and go to college but there's still an 80% unemployment rate because of the challenges they face with social skills and sensory issues," Ms. Scheiner says.\par \par \uc2 She points to the trouble many with Asperger's might have relating to co-workers, forming relationships, or looking people in the eye, often a clincher in a job interview.\par \par \uc2 While there are a number of vocational programs that help people with the developmental disorder train for interviews and workplace situations, Ms. Scheiner says not enough businesses are equipped to respond to Asperger patients.\par \par \uc2 "We're going to focus on employer education to help them understand the challenges individuals face and the accommodations that need to be made, including providing and promoting training colleagues so if they see Asperger behaviors they can understand and respond to them," she says.\par \par \uc2 Ms. Scheiner espouses the economic benefits to the large, national employers she is looking to target: She says individuals with Asperger's tend to be loyal employees and focused.\par \par \uc2 Once they're in an \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  appropriate for them they can be very productive and stay longer in entry-level positions than, say, someone straight out of college, she says.\par \par \uc2 She says the move to hire more people with Asperger's can also help sell a company's \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  agendas and meet diversity targets.\par \par \uc2 "There's a tremendous amount of supply, we are trying to create the same level of employer demand," she says.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=wjco20110222000070"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gmed : \uc2 Medical Conditions | gjob : \uc2 Labor Issues | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gcom : \uc2 Society/Community/Work | ghea : \uc2 Health\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 nyc : \uc2 New York City | usa : \uc2 United States | use : \uc2 Northeast U.S. | usny : \uc2 New York | namz : \uc2 North America\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cell