istribute by email or post to the web.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The jewellery industry is never short of initiatives addressing issues of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The diamond industry led the way 10 years ago, introducing the Kimberley Process to eradicate conflict diamonds.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Gold followed suit with its No Dirty Gold Campaign. The Responsible Jewellery Council, which audits the ethical commitments of jewellery companies, recently signed up both Chanel and the \uc2 Signet Group\uc2  to its certification system.\par \par \uc2 Other organisations protect the interests of different gems, such as the Tanzanite Foundation.\par \par \uc2 Now the UN is getting in on the act, by allying the gem and jewellery industry to its Millennium Development Goals, agreed by 192 countries and 23 organisations in 2000, and the UN Global Compact - 10 principles the UN wants businesses to adopt.\par \par \uc2 The Global Compact principles centre around four main areas: human rights, labour standards and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The result is a new institution in a 17th century building in the heart of Antwerp, the culmination of a brainchild five years in the making.\par \par \uc2 Unitar, the UN Institute for Training and Research is one of the founders of the new International Training Centre on Corporate Opportunities (Ittco) along with the World Jewellery Confederation. Three of the other founders of this institution, which opened its doors in late May, are Belgian - the City of Antwerp, the Antwerp World Diamond Centre and the Flemish government.\par \par \uc2 All Belgian stakeholders are eager to safeguard Antwerp's position at the core of the global diamond industry for generations to come.\par \par \uc2 "Centres of excellence usually aim to drive the UN's social and economic development goals, and most of those linked to the UN have been national or regional, but the Antwerp facility will address the needs of the business sector worldwide," says Ludo van Campenhout, Antwerp's vice mayor with responsibility for diamonds.\par \par \uc2 "Antwerp is a natural choice. We have the largest diamond trading business in the world, with the largest number of accredited, signed-up CSR stakeholders to other initiatives, alongside banks which serve the diamond industry and mining companies," says Marcel Pruwer, an Antwerp-based consultant.\par \par \uc2 The diamond and jewellery sector was one of the first to respond to the call of the UN to ensure that the Millennium Development Goals are generally accepted by 2015.\par \par \uc2 Last September, at the 2010 Shanghai Expo, Carlos Lopos, assistant UN secretary-general, singled out the world jewellery industry, selecting it as a role model for the implementation of CSR by a business sector.\par \par \uc2 For the UN, the Antwerp centre will be a vehicle to train the sector in CSR.\par \par \uc2 For the World Jewellery Confederation, it will serve as a tool to improve consumer confidence in the ethical and environmental practices of the jewellery industry.\par \par \uc2 The centre claims it will tackle the challenge of integrating commitments to environmental sustainability across the gem and jewellery industry worldwide.\par \par \uc2 These include care of the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , contributing to clean water, education, and developing economic infrastructure such as roads, schools and community buildings in areas where raw materials are mined.\par \par \uc2 In practical terms, an educational and professional body, the centre will consult businesses on CSR.\par \par \uc2 It will also offer courses to jewellery businesses on for business leaders and CSR co-ordinators, and management courses for staff members in the sector with a special focus on ethics, and courses in diamond polishing, jewellery design and production.\par \par \uc2 Many top-flight diamond and jewellery companies such as \uc2 Rio Tinto\uc2  and Rosy Blue already have CSR teams in-house and while the Antwerp institute will advise these, it is also designed to cater for those who are now establishing CSR programmes.\par \par \uc2 "This is the first time one central organisation, under the banner of the UN, has created tailored courses, focused on CSR issues, to meet the future needs of the gem and jewellery industry. It is likely to force companies to tackle head-on all issues that threaten the reputation of our industry," says Ya'akov Almor, the Jewellery Council's communications director.\par \par \uc2 "I don't believe any other luxury product industry has done as much to stand up to these challenges," he says.\par \par \uc2 "This means that a person taking a diamond polishing course at Ittco will learn all about the ethics behind the raw materials," he says.\par \par \uc2 "They will understand how the Kimberley Process works, under which circumstances diamonds can be bought and sold and about issues of dirty gold. Ultimately, CSR needs to become part of a company's DNA and all its suppliers, buyers and clients will know how that company implements it."\par \par \uc2 All courses are open to people from anywhere in the world and will eventually include online education.\par \par \uc2 "Ittco's challenge will now be to quickly create a proven track record of diamond and jewellery businesses around the world embracing CSR and implementing the requisite principles in a way that is programmable and replicable," says Mr Pruwer.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 rtnr : \uc2 Signet Jewelers Ltd. | unglmp : \uc2 United Nations Global Compact\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ifinej : \uc2 Fine Jewelry | i491 : \uc2 Jewelry/Silverware | icnp : \uc2 Consumer Products | iluxgds : \uc2 Luxury Goods | i64 : \uc2 Retail/Wholesale | i654 : \uc2 Specialty Stores | i6540028 : \uc2 Jewelry Stores | iretail : \uc2 Retail\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-1